title: BBC Radio 4 - Crisp and Even Brightly (320kbps)
description:
The `true' meaning behind the carol Good King Wenceslas is revealed.

Festive comedy drama by Alick Rowe, with Timothy West, James Holland, June Barrie, William Eedle, Christian Rodska, Michael Tudor Barnes, David March, June Tobin, Maureen O'Brian, Bill Wallis, John Baddeley, Andrew Hilton, Polly James, Anthony Jackson, Paul Nicholson and Michael Deacon


Length: 1:09:28

Created and remastered from two copies, one of which was missing a few minutes and the other of poor quality. The section that was missing previously is in Mono whilst the rest of the play is in Stereo and has been normalised to give a listenable copy. No clicks or cuts. Enjoy!
